</div><p></p><p> Lewis Quigg, the secretary of the Oldham and Saddleworth Conservative Federation, said that despite the complaints to Greater Manchester Police no action was taken. </p><p> Labour supporters would collect signed blank ballot papers from voters, and then fill them in elsewhere. </p><p> He told the Telegraph: “It is an industrial operation the point that you cannot keep up with it. As far as I am aware it has been going on for years. The operation is pretty slick.” </p><p> He said that one Tory candidate in the past had said he would “not stand again because he feels he was cheated of the election”. He named four wards in Oldham where he felt there were “issues”. </p><p> Tom Watson, the Labour deputy leader, said the claims of fraud were “sour grapes”. He said: “It seems like sour grapes to me. If he has got evidence of that he should have told the police immediately. </p><p> “I have talked to our organisers they have got no knowledge of that, if you look at the scale of the result it was pretty decisive and it looks like he was crying over spilt milk there.” </p><p style="margin-top: -20px;"></p><h3 class="was-h4"> How the day unfolded </h3>
<div id="update-20151204-1445" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-1445" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T14:45:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>14:45</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Simon Danczuk: A far-Left candidate would have lost the election for Labour</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Labour won the Oldham by-election because Jim McMahon was a moderate candidate, Rochdale MP Simon Danczuk has said. </p>
<p> Mr McMahon backed Blairite Liz Kendall in the Labour leadership contest, the same candidate that Mr Danczuk favoured. </p>
<p> <span class="ssImg "><img alt="Labour MP for Rochdale, Simon Danczuk" height="387" src="http://i.telegraph.co.uk/multimedia/archive/02584/Simon-Danczuk_2584820b.jpg" version="b" width="620"/><span class="artImageExtras" style="max-width:620px;"><span class="ingCaptionCredit"><span class="caption">Simon Danczuk, Rochdale MP</span><span class="credit">  Photo: Paul Cousans/ZENPIX </span></span></span></span></p>
<p> He told Sky News: "If we'd chosen someone on the far-Left I don't think we would have had the result we had last night" </p>
<p> The MP said Jeremy Corbyn was "wise" to only visit the Oldham West and Royton constituency once, adding: "His name came up not in a good way when I was knocking on the doors. It was right that he stayed away." </p>
</div>
</div><p></p><p>
</p><div id="update-20151204-1331" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
