</p><div id="update-20151204-1041" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-1041" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T10:41:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>10:41</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Questions over voting process</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Nigel Farage might have been criticised for saying that voting in the by-election was "bent" but this latest tweet from LBC's Theo Usherwood sheds more light on the issue. </p>
<p> </p>
<iframe allowfullscreen="true" allowtransparency="true" class="twitter-tweet twitter-tweet-rendered" data-tweet-id="672720514775916544" frameborder="0" id="twitter-widget-4" scrolling="no" style="position: static; visibility: visible; display: block; width: 500px; height: 186px; padding: 0px; border: medium none; max-width: 100%; min-width: 220px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;" title="Twitter Tweet"></iframe>
