</p><div id="update-20151204-2354" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-2354" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T23:54:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>23:54</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Ukip to finish 'a poor second'</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> The Telegraph's Michael Wilkinson writes: </p>
<p> <i>A Lib Dem source tells me that they are expecting Labour to secure more than 60 per cent of the vote with Ukip "a poor second". They added that the other parties, except for the Tories, will also lose their deposits. </i> </p>
<p> <i>They added: "Seriously it's like Pyongyang here. Labour's votes are weighty."</i> </p>
<p> <i>Labour secure just over 54 per cent of the vote at the general election. </i> </p>
<p></p>
<p> <i> </i> </p>
</div>
</div><p></p><p>
</p><div id="update-20151204-2348" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-2348" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T23:48:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>23:48</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Voter turnout 40%</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Oldham count say there's been a 40.26 per cent turn out and 27,795 votes cast, writes Laura Hughes. </p>
<p> <i>That compares to a 60.39 per cent turn out in May's General Election, which saw a majority of 14,738. </i> </p>
<p> <i>Jonathan Ashworth, a Labour frontbencher, tells Newsnight: </i> </p>
<p> <i>"Ukip did well at the general election. They didn’t take seats but they certainly took votes off Labour. </i> </p>
<p> <i>"If they have done that tonight then we need to think about how we take that on. </i> </p>
<p> <i>"But Jim McMahon is a superb candidate and he is going to be a superb MP if he gets elected." </i> </p>
<p></p>
</div>
</div><p></p><p>
</p><div id="update-20151204-2342" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-2342" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T23:42:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>23:42</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Ukip: 'Stop calling our White Christmas van racist'</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Ukip have confirmed a campaign van was playing the song 'White Christmas' whilst out campaigning in Oldham earlier, but said the criticism they have received over the Christmas classic was "ludicrous," Laura Hughes writes. </p>
<p> <i>A spokesperson told the Manchester News: “It was just a Christmas CD. I would be surprised if it was taken in any other way. </i> </p>
<p> <i>“It’s quite sad if you can’t play Christmas songs in December without the Politically Correct brigade picking up on it.”</i> </p>
