</p><div id="update-20151204-2306" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting">
<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-2306" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T23:06:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>23:06</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Farage: If we lose it's because many voters here do not speak English</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Laura Hughes writes: </p>
<p> <i>Nigel Farage has just told ITV News that Ukip are likely to lose because many voters in the area "do not speak English". </i> </p>
<p> <i>Earlier Ukip admitted they believe postal votes have secured Labour victory, but insisted more people have tuned up to the polls to physically vote for them today. </i> </p>
