<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Ukip 'White Christmas van spotted in Royton'</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Some more details on that bizarre tale of a certain yuletide song prompting nose level complaints against Ukip. </p>
<p> It is understood the racket stems from this van, which reportedly "blares out" the tune of White Christmas on the streets of Royton town centre. </p>
<p> Our correspondent Laura Hughes reported earlier that, according to a Ukip spokesman, <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/general-election-2015/parliamentary-constituencies/oldham-west-and-royton/12031040/oldham-west-royton-by-election-results.html#update-20151203-1511">someone had officially complained to the local paper about Ukip campaigning on polling day and playing Bing Crosby's 'White Christmas', which they said was "deeply inappropriate."</a> </p>
<p> <i>Have you spotted Ukip's White Christmas van? Email james.rothwell@telegraph.co.uk</i> </p>
