<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-1658" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T16:58:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>17.31</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">Ukip embroiled in 'White Christmas' row</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> This just in from Laura Hughes, our political correspondent in Oldham: </p>
<p> <i><span class="ssImg left"><img alt="Quote" height="40" src="http://i.telegraph.co.uk/multimedia/archive/01817/quotes_1817837a.gif" version="" width="45"/><span class="artImageExtras" style="max-width:45px;"><span class="ingCaptionCredit"></span></span></span> A Ukip spokesperson tells me they have 200- 250 people out campaigning for them today. </i> </p>
<p> <i>They also said someone has officially complained to the local paper about Ukip campaigning on polling day and playing Bing Crosby's 'White Christmas', which they said was "deeply inappropriate."</i> </p>
<p> <i>The spokesperson said tonight is going to be a "cracking success" whether they win or not. </i> </p>
<p> <i>"Labour have really swamped the two South Asian wards because the postal turn out was very low and they were relying on that", they told me. </i> </p>
<p> <i>"In balance it's still likely to be Labour, but we've given them a right run for their money."</i> </p>
<p> <i>Whilst they said Corbyn has been "toxic", the spokesperson said a year ago Miliband was equally unpopular and this is a "malaise" in Labour, not just amongst it's Leaders. </i> </p>
<p> <i>"We are having fun", they added. </i> </p>
