<h3 class="was-h6"> <a href="#update-20151204-1701" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.url"> <time datetime="2015-12-04T17:01:00+00:00" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.datePublished"></time> <span>17:01</span> </a> </h3>
<h3 class="was-h3" itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.headline">...and Margot Parker is not far behind him</h3>
<div itemprop="liveBlogUpdate.articleBody">
<p> Margot Parker, Ukip's MEP for the East Midlands is also out campaigning in Oldham today, Laura Hughes reports. </p>
<p> <i>She told me: "People aren't speaking about Corbyn, they are speaking about Labour and have almost airbrushed him. </i> </p>
<p> <i>"They aren't mentioning him, it's about 'what have Labour done for us?' They are very dissatisfied with Labour more generally and Ukip is the natural party for them."</i> </p>
<p> <i>A Local fishmonger tells me there's been some excitement around the election because of Nigel Farage's visit this week and the national media attention. </i> </p>
<p> <i>But he added that he wouldn't be voting as "all politicians are the same."</i> </p>
