<p></p>
<p> This is a disaster for Labour. It's Jeremy Corbyn's <a href="http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/battle-of-waterloo/11676475/The-Battle-of-Waterloo-as-it-happened-on-June-18-1815.html" target="_blank">equivalent of Waterloo</a> – only without the preceding ten years where he wins any battles at all. It's the party's worst vote share since 1918. </p>
<p> Such a national swing would be catastrophic, leaving the Conservatives with 394 MPs, which would easily dwarf Labour's 160-strong cohort. </p>
<p> So let's imagine what could happen if the swing to Ukip was so bad that Labour actually lost the seat. </p>
<p>
<link href="http://s.telegraph.co.uk/graphics/MobileSwitcher/v2/assets/embed.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"/></p>
<div class="tgs__wrapper" id="tg-ms-2473"><object class="tgs__image" data="http://s.telegraph.co.uk/graphics/MobileSwitcher/v2/images/2473-14490548911573051722.svg" type="image/svg+xml"></object></div>
